{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778979839911,"sessionID":"ses_1cc8adaffffeOPVA3ToAxBQ6Os","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_ifaBTu1atOKQLKdb0rVery2m","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"obo-grep.pl -r 'term_tracker_item|created_by: dragon-ai-agent|dc-contributor https://orcid.org' src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo","timeout":120000,"workdir":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon","description":"Inspect current metadata patterns"},"output":"...output truncated...\n\nFull output saved to: /github/home/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_e33761f8b001OvmX0xScocrY9Q\n\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600023\nname: placental villous stroma\ndef: \"A stroma that is part of a chorionic villus (placental villus). A placental villous stroma supports the fetal capillaries and villous trophoblast.\" [PMID:31512233]\nsynonym: \"chorionic villous stroma\" EXACT [PMID:12624135]\nsynonym: \"CVS\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [PMID:12624135]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0003891 ! stroma\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0007106 ! chorionic villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-07-04T10:46:17Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600024\nname: pulmonary venule\ndef: \"A venule that is part of a lung and drains oxygenated blood from pulmonary capillaries. A pulmonary venule merges into a pulmonary vein branch that runs in the pulmonary interlobular septa.\" [PMID:22283705, PMID:30247823]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001979 ! venule\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0002048 ! lung\nrelationship: connected_to UBERON:0002016 ! pulmonary vein\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0013127 ! pulmonary venous system\nrelationship: vessel_drains_blood_from UBERON:0016405 ! pulmonary capillary\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-10-24T11:26:27Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600025\nname: intervillous space\ndef: \"An anatomical space that separates the basal plate and the chorionic plate. The intervillous space is filled with endometrial gland secretions during early stages of the pregnancy and later perfused with maternal blood, bathing the chorionic villous tree.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:32108320]\nis_a: UBERON:0000464 ! anatomical space\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:8600038 ! placental disc\nrelationship: surrounds UBERON:8600026 ! chorionic villous tree\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T11:50:32Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600026\nname: chorionic villous tree\ndef: \"A tree-like structure formed by chorionic villi that sprouts from the chorionic plate in the placental disc. The arborous shape of the chorionic villous tree provides maximal contact area with maternal blood in the intervillous space.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nsynonym: \"placental villous tree\" EXACT [PMID:9260835]\nsynonym: \"villous tree\" BROAD [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nis_a: UBERON:0000061 ! anatomical structure\nrelationship: composed_primarily_of UBERON:0007106 ! chorionic villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:8600038 ! placental disc\nrelationship: proximally_connected_to UBERON:0004027 ! chorionic plate\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T11:57:24Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600027\nname: chorionic stem villus\ndef: \"A chorionic villus that provides structural support to the villous tree. A chorionic stem villus is characterized by a condensed fibrous stroma in which fetal arteries, veins, arterioles, and venules are embedded. It represents a distributing framework for fetal chorionic circulation, supplying the floating villi. It can exhibit a diameter ranging from approximately 3000 μm (trunci near the chorionic plate) to 80 μm (smallest ramuli chorii).\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:9260835]\nsynonym: \"placental stem villus\" EXACT [PMID:9260835]\nis_a: UBERON:0007106 ! chorionic villus\nrelationship: branching_part_of UBERON:8600026 ! chorionic villous tree\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:8600029 ! chorionic immature intermediate villus\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T13:00:59Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600028\nname: chorionic mesenchymal villus\ndef: \"The first generation of a tertiary villus that is derived from a syncytial sprout by the invasion of the mesenchyme, in which blood vessels differentiate through vasculogenesis, and gradually transforms into a new immature intermediate villus. A chorionic mesenchymal villus has a thick trophoblastic covering, and cytotrophoblast cells are interposed between syncytium and the trophoblastic basal lamina over 50–100% of the surface. The stroma is characterized by loosely arranged collagen fibers that enmesh mesenchymal and some villous macrophages. The fetal capillaries are poorly developed.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nsynonym: \"mesenchymal villus\" BROAD [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nis_a: UBERON:0009995 ! tertiary chorionic villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T13:38:12Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600029\nname: chorionic immature intermediate villus\ndef: \"A bulbous, immature chorionic villus that is formed of loose connective tissue with few fetal vessels. A chorionic immature intermediate villus develops from a chorionic mesenchymal villus, and is the forerunner of a chorionic stem villus.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:487407, PMID:9260835]\nsynonym: \"immature intermediate villus\" RELATED [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:21452443]\nis_a: UBERON:0007106 ! chorionic villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:8600028 ! chorionic mesenchymal villus\nrelationship: develops_into UBERON:8600027 ! chorionic stem villus\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T13:41:05Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600030\nname: chorionic terminal villus\ndef: \"The most distal part of a chorionic villus. A chorionic terminal villus is a grape-like structure characterized by a high degree of capillarization and highly dilated sinusoids. A terminal villus has less stroma and a discontinuous cytotrophoblast layer, and contains 4–6 fetal capillaries per cross section. It exhibits a diameter ranging from 40 to about 80 μm.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:21452443]\nsynonym: \"terminal villus\" BROAD [PMID:21452443]\nis_a: UBERON:8600032 ! chorionic floating villus\nrelationship: branching_part_of UBERON:8600026 ! chorionic villous tree\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T13:41:16Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600031\nname: chorionic mature intermediate villus\ndef: \"A slender branch of a chorionic stem villus. A chorionic mature intermediate villus lacks fetal arterioles and venules in the stroma, which is composed of slender fetal capillaries embedded into a loose connective tissue that is rich in cells but poor in fibers. It exhibits a diameter ranging from 60 to about 100 μm.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:21452443]\nsynonym: \"mature intermediate villus\" BROAD [PMID:21452443]\nis_a: UBERON:8600032 ! chorionic floating villus\nrelationship: branching_part_of UBERON:8600026 ! chorionic villous tree\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: proximally_connected_to UBERON:8600027 ! chorionic stem villus\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T13:41:28Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600032\nname: chorionic floating villus\ndef: \"A chorionic villus that is not attached to the placental basal plate and it is immersed in maternal blood.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:31870762, PMID:32513715]\nsynonym: \"floating villus\" BROAD [PMID:31870762]\nsynonym: \"free-floating villus\" BROAD [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nis_a: UBERON:0007106 ! chorionic villus\nrelationship: branching_part_of UBERON:8600026 ! chorionic villous tree\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T13:42:09Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600033\nname: chorionic anchoring villus\ndef: \"A distal smaller chorionic stem villus that is connected to the maternal side of the placenta (in early gestational stages to the decidua, and later to the developing basal plate) via a cytotrophoblast cell column. A chorionic anchoring villus stabilizes the position of the villous tree in the maternal intervillous bloodstream.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8, PMID:15142834, PMID:32513715, PMID:9260835]\nsynonym: \"anchoring villus\" BROAD [PMID:15142834]\nis_a: UBERON:8600027 ! chorionic stem villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2023-12-12T13:42:20Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600034\nname: jejunum lamina propria\ndef: \"A lamina propria that is part of a jejunum.\" [PMID:9394954]\nsynonym: \"jejunal lamina propria\" EXACT [PMID:1556433]\nsynonym: \"lamina propria of jejunum\" EXACT [PMID:22763879]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0000030 ! lamina propria\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0002115 ! jejunum\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8134-3037\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0008343 ! intestinal villus of jejunum\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-09T16:36:35Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600035\nname: ileum lamina propria\ndef: \"A lamina propria that is part of an ileum.\" [PMID:29316348]\nsynonym: \"ileal lamina propria\" EXACT [PMID:37467267]\nsynonym: \"lamina propria of ileum\" EXACT [PMID:36067905]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0000030 ! lamina propria\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0002116 ! ileum\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-8134-3037\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0008344 ! intestinal villus of ileum\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-09T16:48:17Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600036\nname: kidney loop of Henle long descending thin limb outer medulla\ndef: \"A section of the long descending thin limb of the loop of Henle that is part of the outer medulla of the kidney.\" [PMID:33769951]\nsynonym: \"DTL2\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [PMID:33769951]\nsynonym: \"long descending limb of the loop of Henle in the outer medulla\" EXACT [PMID:33769951]\nis_a: UBERON:0000064 ! organ part\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001293 ! outer medulla of kidney\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0005100 ! long descending thin limb\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-15T13:28:03Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600037\nname: kidney loop of Henle long descending thin limb inner medulla\ndef: \"A section of the long descending thin limb of the loop of Henle that is part of the inner medulla of the kidney.\" [PMID:33769951]\nsynonym: \"DTL3\" RELATED OMO:0003000 [PMID:33769951]\nsynonym: \"long descending limb of the loop of Henle in the inner medulla\" EXACT [PMID:33769951]\nis_a: UBERON:0000064 ! organ part\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001294 ! inner medulla of kidney\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0005100 ! long descending thin limb\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-15T13:32:25Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600038\nname: placental disc\ndef: \"A disc-shaped structure that is part of the placenta. A placental disc supports fetal development through the exchange of nutrients between maternal and fetal bloodstreams. The placental disc is structured to keep the blood streams separate, while maximizing surface area for the transport of nutrients between them, to maintain an immunological barrier.\" [PMID:35496035]\nsynonym: \"placental disk\" EXACT [PMID:30133439]\nis_a: UBERON:0000061 ! anatomical structure\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001987 ! placenta\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-16T17:50:20Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600039\nname: chorionic villous mesenchyme\ndef: \"A mesenchyme that is part of a chorionic villus.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0003104 ! mesenchyme\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0007106 ! chorionic villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-16T18:13:12Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600040\nname: chorionic stem villous blood vessel\ndef: \"A blood vessel that is part of a chorionic stem villus.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nsynonym: \"stem villous vessel\" BROAD [PMID:7547738]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001981 ! blood vessel\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:8600027 ! chorionic stem villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-16T18:14:32Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600041\nname: chorionic terminal villous capillary\ndef: \"A capillary that is part of a chorionic terminal villus. This capillary is generally narrow, but displays sinusoidal dilations along its length, often at the points of acute bends. These dilations bring the capillary endothelium into close contact with the overlying syncytiotrophoblast to form a vasculosyncytial membrane.\" [doi:10.1007/978-3-030-84725-8]\nsynonym: \"terminal villous capillary\" BROAD [PMID:22461195]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001982 ! capillary\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:8600030 ! chorionic terminal villus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-16T18:16:47Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600042\nname: endometrial lymphatic vessel\ndef: \"A lymphatic vessel that is part of an endometrium.\" [PMID:23054374]\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001473 ! lymphatic vessel\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0001295 ! endometrium\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-01-16T18:18:36Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600043\nname: lateral wall of urinary bladder\ndef: \"A wall of the urinary bladder that is situated on the sides or flanks.\" [PMID:30548115]\nxref: FMA:15905\nis_a: UBERON:0001256 ! wall of urinary bladder\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6677-8489 ! Aleix Puig-Barbé\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7655-4833 ! Ellen Quardokus\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4341-3265\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2804-127X ! Sanjay Jain\nproperty_value: dcterms-date \"2024-02-29T10:09:51Z\" xsd:dateTime\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8600044\nname: left lateral wall of urinary bladder\ndef: \"A lateral wall of the urinary bladder that is located on the left side.\" [PMID:30548115]\nsynonym: \"left wall of bladder\" BROAD [PMID:32233638]\nsynonym: \"left wall of urinary bladder\" EXACT [FMA:15907]\